              "origin": "syntopicon",
              "content": "<p> Titus Flavius Josephus (37 CE- ca. 100 CE) was a famous Jewish historian of the Roman Empire. He was named at birth Yosef ben Matityahu and claimed priestly descent on his father’s side and royal Davidic descent on his mother’s side. His works <em>Jewish Antiquities</em> and <em>The Jewish War</em> are invaluable sources of information for the history of Judaism and early Christianity. </p>",
